-- Plastikkart Jumps in Istanbul After Starting Gemalto Talks
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-03-28T15:18:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/plastikkart-jumps-in-istanbul-after-starting-gemalto-talks-1-.html
Plastikkart Akilli Kart Iletisim
Sistemleri Sanayi & Ticaret AS (PKART) , a Turkish maker of smart cards,
climbed in Istanbul after starting talks with Amsterdam-based
Gemalto NV on a possible share sale.  Plastikkart rose 3.3 percent to 2.85 liras by the close of
trading after jumping as much as 8.3 percent. The company will
hold talks with Gemalto on a possible share sale and commercial
partnership, it said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benjamin Harvey at 
